    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Standard">
        <prj:name>j1256</prj:name>
        <prj:note>
Continuum map using band 7 with a sensitivity of 26.7 microJy. The target is a planetary system formed by a primary object with a mass at the substellar limit and a giant planet of 11 Mjup separated 8 arcsec (102 AU) from the primary. ALMA will point to the central coordinates so that the two objects will be explored simultaneously in one single pointing. We request an angular resolution of 0.5 arcsec and an angular scale of 2 arcsec or better.

Since the main objective is to detect the continuum emission from the disk, the correlator setup makes use of full continuum sensitivity. However, we can get a bonus on the potential scientific outcome of the project by also measuring the CO 3-2 line at 345 ghz (free of charge) in one of the basebands with a spectral resolution below 1 km/s without any loss in the continuum sensitivity. We have chosen the spectral line observing mode with baseband 1 in the signal band centered at the rest frequency of the CO 3-2 line covering a bandwidth of 1.875 GHz with a resolution of 0.98 km/s (after averaging 2 channels). Baseband 2 has been centered 1.8 GHz above baseband 1 to cover 1.875 GHz at a resolution 27.2 km/s. The other two basebands have been centered at the corresponding image band frequencies. The image band was selected 12 GHz above the signal band to minimize the possible effects of the atmospheric water vapor line at 325 GHz. The final continuum will be obtained by averaging all channels except for those of the CO line in case it is detected.
</prj:note>
