    <prp:abstract>We propose to search for the presence of cold debris disks in the recently 
discovered planetary system VHS J125601.92-125723.9 formed by a primary at the 
substellar mass limit (73 Mjup) and a giant planet of 11 Mjup separated by 8" 
or 102 AU at the very near distance of 12.7 pc. The age of the wide planetary 
system is constrained to be 150-300 Myr. The requested ALMA observations using 
band 7 will allow us to detect the thermal emission of cold dust with 
disk-to-object mass ratio of the order of 10^-9 (like the Saturn-ring system) 
that could be surrounding the primary component, the planet, or both. This 
exceptional system may provide significant insight into the formation, 
evolution, and architecture of planetary systems</prp:abstract>
